# RZGB Project ‚Äî Cursor Rules

Read `.ai-context.md` in the root before doing anything. It has the full session history, file map, and known issues.

---

## Project Identity

Two brands, one codebase:
- **Zaproc** (`zaproc.co.uk`) ‚Äî SaaS procurement platform
- **RZ Global Solutions** (`rzglobalsolutions.co.uk`) ‚Äî manufacturing broker

Domain routing is done at **runtime** in `src/lib/portalConfig.js` via `window.location.hostname`. Never use build-time env vars for domain switching.

---

## Stack Rules

- **React 18 + Vite** ‚Äî JSX only, no TypeScript
- **Tailwind CSS** for all styling ‚Äî no inline styles, no CSS modules
- **Radix UI + shadcn** for UI primitives ‚Äî check `src/components/ui/` before creating new components
- **Lucide React** for icons ‚Äî do not import from other icon libraries
- **Framer Motion** for animations
- **React Router v6** ‚Äî use `useNavigate`, `useLocation`, `<Link>` ‚Äî no `window.location` for internal routing
- **Supabase** for auth + DB ‚Äî always scope queries with `workspace_id`

---

## File Conventions

- Pages go in `src/pages/`
- Shared components go in `src/components/`
- Auth, theme, admin, supplier, client state live in `src/contexts/`
- Domain/portal logic lives ONLY in `src/lib/portalConfig.js`
- Import alias `@/` maps to `src/` ‚Äî always use it, never relative `../../`

---

## Auth & Security Rules

- Never bypass RLS ‚Äî always filter by `workspace_id` in queries
- `supabaseAdmin.js` uses the service role key ‚Äî only use it for operations blocked by RLS (supplier status updates etc.) ‚Äî never for reads a regular user could do
- Never commit `.env` ‚Äî it is gitignored intentionally
- Roles: `super_admin` > `customer_admin` > `client` > `supplier` ‚Äî check `ProtectedRoute` before adding new protected pages

---

## Domain Routing Rules

- `isLandingDomain()` ‚Üí zaproc.co.uk
- `isRZGBDomain()` ‚Üí rzglobalsolutions.co.uk
- `isAnyLandingDomain()` ‚Üí either landing domain
- `getPortalUrl(path)` ‚Üí builds correct URL for portal links from landing domains
- `DomainGuard` wraps the entire router ‚Äî redirects non-root paths on landing domains to `portal.zaproc.co.uk`
- `HomeOrRedirect` at `"/"` ‚Äî picks which landing page to show based on domain

---

## Styling Rules

- Light theme is default ‚Äî dark mode via ThemeContext only if user toggled
- Glassmorphism on RZGB: `backdrop-blur`, `bg-white/10`, `border border-white/20`
- RZGB color palette: slate (`slate-900`, `slate-700`) + orange accent (`orange-500`, `orange-400`)
- Zaproc color palette: sky blue + slate (monochrome professional)
- Font: Inter (headings) + DM Sans (body) ‚Äî already loaded in `index.html`
- Never hardcode colors as hex ‚Äî use Tailwind classes

---

## Git Workflow

- `main` is protected ‚Äî never push directly, always use a PR
- PRs require GitHub Actions `Build` + `Lint` checks to pass
- Branch naming: `feat/`, `fix/`, `chore/` prefixes
- Commit style: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `ci:`, `refactor:`

---

## Deployment

- Hostinger auto-deploys from `main` branch
- Both sites (zaproc + rzglobalsolutions) deploy from the same repo
- Build: `npm run build` ‚Üí `dist/`
- Env vars (`VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`) must be set in Hostinger dashboard ‚Äî they are NOT in git
- `.htaccess` in `public/` handles SPA routing on Apache ‚Äî do not delete it

---

## Do Not

- Do not add TypeScript ‚Äî project is JSX only
- Do not use CSS files or styled-components ‚Äî Tailwind only
- Do not import from `react-icons` ‚Äî use `lucide-react`
- Do not use `window.location.href` for internal navigation ‚Äî use React Router
- Do not create new Supabase clients ‚Äî use `supabase` from `src/lib/supabase.js` or `supabaseAdmin` from `src/lib/supabaseAdmin.js`
- Do not commit `.env`, secrets, or service role keys
- Do not add `console.log` in production code
